caption.text:
👀Looking for a 🍏vegetarian friendly dish that's EASY to make at 🏠home? This Lo Mein is 😍TO DIE FOR. Get the recipe by Damn Delicious 
INGREDIENTS:

8 ounces lo mein egg noodles*
1 tablespoon olive oil
2 cloves garlic, minced
2 cups cremini mushrooms, sliced
1 red bell pepper, julienned
1 carrot, julienned
1/2 cup snow peas
3 cups baby spinach
FOR THE SAUCE
2 tablespoons reduced sodium soy sauce, or more, to taste
2 teaspoons sugar
1 teaspoon sesame oil
1/2 teaspoon ground ginger
1/2 teaspoon Sriracha, or more, to taste

DIRECTIONS:
In a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce, sugar, sesame oil, ginger and Sriracha; set aside.
In a large pot of boiling water, cook noodles according to package instructions; drain well.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium high heat. Add garlic, mushrooms, bell pepper and carrot. Cook, stirring frequently, until tender, about 3-4 minutes. Stir in snow peas and spinach until the spinach has wilted, about 2-3 minutes.
Stir in egg noodles and soy sauce mixture, and gently toss to combine. Serve immediately.

caption.text:
🥂 Morgen is alles tiptop in orde, zeker met deze hemelse pralines van gerookte eendenborst, Breydelhammousse en speculaas.  Ontdek het receptje 👇:
●
🧂 Ingrediënten voor 8 personen 🧂
- 8 sneetjes gerookte eendenborst
- 1 zakje Breydelhammousse
- fijngemalen speculaas
- fijngehakte rozemarijn ● 🔪 Bereidingswijze 🔪
- Leg de sneetjes eendenborst open op een plank. Spuit er aan één kant een toefje Breydelhammousse op.
- Rol de sneetjes eendenborst op rond de Breydelhammousse
- Dop de buitenste kanten van de pralines in de fijngemalen speculaas
- Werk het geheel af met fijngehakte rozemarijn. ●

Smakelijk! ●

#breydel #fingerlickingfood #cooking #nye #recept #recipe
#proefgezelligheid #beleefbreydel ● 🥂 Demain, tout sera parfait grâce à ces divines pralines au magret de canard fumé, à la mousse de jambon Breydel et au spéculoos. Découvrez la recette 👇:
🧂 Ingrédients pour 8 personnes 🧂
- 8 tranches de magret de canard fumé
- 1 poche de mousse de jambon Breydel
- Du spéculoos moulu - Du romarin finement haché ● 🔪 Préparation 🔪
- Ouvrez les tranches de magret de canard sur une planche. Versez d'un côté une rosette de mousse de jambon Breydel.
- Roulez les tranches de magret autour de la mousse de jambon Breydel - Trempez les côtés extérieurs des pralines dans le spéculoos moulu - Garnissez le tout avec un peu de romarin haché. ●

Bon appétit ! ●

caption.text:
Fans of Right Gin may have noticed some changes to our packaging over the years. While the old bottle was beautiful, as bartenders began to incorporate Right into more and more exciting craft cocktails, they started to request a bottle that was easier to pick up, hold, use, and even store on the bar itself. ⁠
⁠
When we received this feedback, we got to work selecting a bottle that would be beautiful, well-balanced for repetitive movements throughout a bartending shift, and ideal for creating delicious craft cocktails. We also wanted to be sure the diameter opening would fit the standard black pour spout snugly, to prevent leaking or slipping - a common oversight of many other bottles on the backbar and bar rail. At the end of the day, we realized that the right shape, size, and type of bottle was essential for RIGHT Gin, because “Est Unus Modus Verus” - there IS a RIGHT Way. ⁠
⁠
